  "roast_critique": "Liam, your résumé reads like a BuzzFeed list of every business‑analysis buzzword you could cram into one page. The opening line – “Strategic Business Analyst with 7 years of experience turning data‑driven insights into actionable growth plans” – is about as original as a LinkedIn headline generator. You brag about $3 M+ cost savings and a $2.1 M upsell hunt, yet you never explain the *problem* you solved, just the shiny numbers. The “References: Available upon request” line is the 1990s equivalent of saying “I’ll get back to you later.” Also, your LinkedIn URL is missing the https:// prefix, as if you expect recruiters to read your mind. Finally, you sprinkle in a mountain of tools (Power BI, Tableau, Looker, Azure Data Factory, RPA bots) without prioritizing the ones that matter for the job you’re after – it looks more like a grocery list than a focused skill set.",
  "professional_suggestions": [
    "Rewrite the Professional Summary into a punchy 2‑sentence value proposition that highlights a single, concrete achievement (e.g., the $3 M cost‑saving project) and the specific role you’re targeting.",
    "Remove the outdated \"References: Available upon request\" line; instead, add a short line directing readers to your LinkedIn profile (with full https:// URL) or a portfolio/GitHub link showcasing your Power BI dashboards and automation scripts.",
    "Prioritize and group your technical skills – keep the top 5 most relevant tools for the target role and move peripheral items (R, VBA, Snowflake basics) to an optional “Additional Skills” section, and add a bullet that demonstrates soft‑skill impact (e.g., stakeholder negotiation that led to the 14 % contract‑value lift)."
