  "roast_critique": "David, your résumé reads like a designer’s version of a motivational poster that was printed on a cheap printer. The career objective is a re‑hashed LinkedIn tagline – \"Creative UX/UI Designer… Passionate about user research, visual storytelling, and accessibility\" – as if you’ve never heard those buzzwords before. You even managed to forget proper capitalization on the first bullet of your senior role (\"led redesign of a fintech mobile app\"), which makes the whole thing look like a hastily typed Slack message. Your portfolio URL is just \"davidlui.design\" without the https:// prefix, assuming recruiters will magically know where to click. And of course you close with the fossilized \"References: Provided upon request\" line, which screams you haven’t updated your copy in a decade. All those impressive numbers are hidden behind a sea of generic phrasing, so a hiring manager wonders whether you’re a seasoned designer or just a walking collection of industry clichés.",
