{
  "roast_critique": "Ethan, your résumé screams \"engineer’s buzzword bingo\" louder than a turbine at full throttle. Opening with the vague Objective – “Mechanical Design Engineer with 6 years of experience … Seeking a senior engineering role where innovative engineering drives sustainability and reliability” – is about as specific as a weather forecast. The bullet “reducing weight by 18 % while meeting fatigue‑life targets (>10⁶ cycles)” sounds impressive until you realize you never say *why* that mattered to the program’s cost or performance. Likewise, “achieving a 12 % increase in thrust efficiency” is dropped without any context about fuel savings or mission impact. Your \"Managed a multidisciplinary team of 5 engineers and 3 technicians, establishing stage‑gate reviews that cut design iteration time by 27 %\" is the only hint of leadership, yet the rest of the document is a laundry‑list of tools (SolidWorks, CATIA, ANSYS, etc.) that reads like a software inventory rather than a story. And of course, you close with the fossils‑level \"References available upon request,\" as if recruiters are still using fax machines. In short, you’ve packed the page with metrics and acronyms but left out the human narrative that actually sells a candidate.",
  "professional_suggestions": [
    "Rewrite the Objective into a punchy 2‑sentence value proposition that quantifies a specific business impact (e.g., “Delivered X% weight reduction in turbine blades, saving $Y million annually”) and eliminates generic buzzwords.",
    "For each quantified achievement, add a brief business context (cost savings, performance gains, sustainability impact) and sprinkle in soft‑skill highlights such as cross‑functional leadership, stakeholder communication, or mentorship to balance the heavy technical focus.",
    "Remove the outdated \"References available upon request\" line; instead, include a short link to a professional portfolio or a statement like \"References available on request via LinkedIn\" and consider adding a concise \"Key Leadership & Communication\" bullet to showcase your people skills."
  ],
  "rating": 8
}
